Danielle Ockwell, who was Lord's subordinate and asked for child safety training because she was concerned about his behavior, testified that Jacqui Barnat, the head of the services for children at the YMCA association in Caringbah, who was Lord's superior, was "very intimidating and it was often difficult to talk to him about anything."
The CEO said he did not accept evidence from the staff, that they felt uneasy if they were to contact their superiors and report the deeds.
