Mr. Hare said he had told the YMCA Council in New South Wales that the lesson of Jonathan Lord's "the case of Jonathan Lord" for the organization was that the staff "did not submit any message" and the council agreed to him.
Mr. Hare said the decision to have the staff signed the unsupervised agreements shortly after the allegations were made by the general manager for services to children at YMCA, Liam Whitley.
He said the goal was to avoid the breach of evidence, but was "overly zealous" and poorly executed.
