Arctic Monkeys postponed Glasgow concert due to Alex Turner's illness
Rock band Arctic Monkeys moved the concert in Glasgow after the lead singer was diagnosed with lap inflammation.
Sheffield Group was scheduled to perform at the city's Hydro complex on Friday.
The illness of the main singer Alex Turner, forced her to move the performance.
The group's announcement came after it was similarly forced to postpone Thursday's performance at the LG Arena in Birmingham.
In a statement on its official website, Arctic Monkeys says: "Following the decision to postpone today's performance at the LG Arena in Birmingham and on the basis of a medical recommendation, Arctic Monkeys, the Arctic Monkeys group must also postpone the performance at the Hydro complex in Glasgow scheduled for Friday, November 1."
"Alex Turner has been diagnosed with inflammation of the larynx and unfortunately he will not be able to get off."
